C. Performance — consolidar RLS duplicadas:

En tools, categories, deals, affiliate_links, tool_categories hay dos políticas SELECT (admin + public) que se evalúan ambas en cada query. Reemplazar:

drop policy if exists "admins manage tools" on tools;
drop policy if exists "public can read active tools" on tools;
create policy "tools_select" on tools for select
  using (status = 'active' or public.is_admin());
create policy "tools_write" on tools for all
  using (public.is_admin()) with check (public.is_admin());
Repetir el patrón para categories, deals, affiliate_links, tool_categories.

→ Reduce overhead RLS a la mitad en queries del directorio.

D. Nuevos campos útiles en tools (sin tags):

alter table tools
  add column if not exists last_enriched_at timestamptz,
  add column if not exists featured_priority int default 0,
  add column if not exists search_tsv tsvector
    generated always as (
      to_tsvector('english',
        coalesce(name,'') || ' ' ||
        coalesce(short_description,'') || ' ' ||
        coalesce(full_description,'') || ' ' ||
        coalesce(best_for,''))
    ) stored;

create index if not exists tools_search_tsv_idx on tools using gin(search_tsv);
create index if not exists tools_featured_idx on tools(featured_priority desc) where status='active';
→ search_tsv habilita full-text search rápido en el directorio (ej: where search_tsv @@ plainto_tsquery('email automation')).

